    "response": " Kubernetes is a container orchestration platform that automates deployment, scaling, and management of applications written in containerized technologies such as Docker.\n\n\n\nIn a world-renowned Robotics Engineering company, they are developing five different types of robots for various tasks - RobotA, RobotB, RobotC, RobotD, and RobotE. Each robot is designed to work in a specific environment - Landscape, Water, Sky, Desert, or Space. The team decides to use Kubernetes to manage the deployment and operations of these robots across multiple servers. \n\nThe following pieces of information are known:\n1) The robot designed for the Sky does not have an AI assistant.\n2) RobotB is deployed on a different server from the one where RobotD is managed.\n3) The robot designed for the Water environment has its own Kubernetes pod, and it's not RobotA or RobotC.\n4) In the Desert, neither of the robots with AI assistants are placed.\n5) RobotE uses the same Kubernetes pod as the one where RobotB is deployed.\n6) The robot designed for Landscape environment has its own Kubernetes Pod and it's not RobotA or RobotC.\n7) There isn't a RobotD in the Sky, but there is on the server where RobotE resides.\n8) RobotA doesn\u2019t operate in Water.\n9) The robot designed for Space does not have its own Kubernetes pod.\n10) Only one robot, which is not RobotC or RobotB, operates in Landscape environment and uses Kubernetes pod as well. \n\nQuestion: Which robot has the AI assistant? And where are they deployed?\n\n\nFrom clue 1 we know that the Sky robot doesn\u2019t have an AI assistant. Hence, it can't be RobotA or RobotB (as per clues 2 and 3) nor RobotC, RobotD or RobotE. So, by elimination, this must be RobotD or RobotE. But from clue 7, RobotD is in the Desert. Therefore, the robot in Sky environment has to be RobotE.\n \nFrom clue 5, we know that RobotB uses the same Kubernetes pod as RobotE (Sky). This means RobotB is also in Sky. So now, only RobotA and RobotC are left for the Landscape environment (clue 6). But from clue 8, RobotA doesn't operate in Water. As the robot operating in the Landscape has its own Kubernetes pod (clue 7), RobotA can't operate there. Hence, RobotC operates in the Landscape environment and it's using Kubernetes pod.\n \nFrom step 2, we know that RobotB uses the same Kubernetes pod as RobotE. So, RobotB also has an AI assistant since robot deployed on this server also has AI (clue 3).\n\nAnswer: Both RobotB and RobotD have AI assistants. They are deployed in the Sky environment.\n",
